Name: retroperitoneal hemangiopericytoma
Definition: A hemangiopericytoma that is manifested in the breast.

Name: conventional malignant hemangiopericytoma
Definition: An arthritis that is an autoimmune disease which develops due to an infection located elsewhere in the body.

Name: malignant mediastinum hemangiopericytoma
Definition: A hemangiopericytoma and sarcoma of the mediastinum that is located_in the mediastinum.

Name: obsolete simian acquired immunodeficiency syndrome
Definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection in primates and monkeys

Name: adult malignant hemangiopericytoma
Definition: A malignant ovarian germ cell neoplasm that is a teratoma containing variable amounts of immature (typically primitive/embryonal neuroectodermal) tissues

Name: childhood malignant hemangiopericytoma
Definition: An adolescence-adult electroclinical syndrome starting in adolescence exhibiting generalized tonic-clonic seizures as the only seizure type.
